Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Cut the @sweet potato{2} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Toss with @oil{}, @salt{}, @pepper{} and half the @paprika{1%sachet}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. You want them well spaced out to achieve a crispy finish.

== Burgers ==

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with @water{2%tsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Add the @Irish beef mince{250%g} and @chorizo{100%g}. Season with @pepper{} and mix everything together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, then form into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the chorizo and beef burgers until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins and lower heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Place some @grated cheese{50%g} on top of each burger.

Cover the pan and set aside (off the heat) until the cheese has melted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Caramelised Onion ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry until soft and sweet, stirring occasionally, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add half the @balsamic glaze{1%sachet} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}.

Cook until the balsamic has evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the remaining @paprika{1%sachet} with the @aioli{1%sachet}.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}(thinly sliced).

Reserve a few @salad leaves{40%g} for the burgers and toss the remaining salad leaves with the tomatoes, @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}, a drizzle of @oil{}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

To assemble the burgers, spread a spoonful of paprika aioli over each base bun.

Top with the reserved leaves, tomato slices, cheesy chorizo and beef burger and caramelised onion.

Close with the top bun.

Serve with sweet potato fries, salad and remaining aioli alongside.